# QA checklist maintenance

When you add or change **anything customers or salon users see or do** (screens, steps, emails, permissions, embed, booking rules, dashboard sections), update **`QA_QC_CHECKLIST.md`** in the same release:

- Add new checkboxes in plain language (no code terms, no file names).
- Adjust or remove items if behavior was removed or replaced.
- Bump the “Last reviewed against the app” date when you do a full pass.

The checklist is for **non-technical** QA testers; keep wording simple and outcome-focused (“user sees…”, “email arrives…”, “button saves…”).
